## Election

### Day 1: 6 November 2014

The initial day of voting, 6 November 2014, saw a flurry of activity as the [Security Council](/Security_Council) and the [General Assembly](/United_Nations_General_Assembly) commenced their independent ballots. The objective was clear: elect five judges to the International Court of Justice. The process involved multiple rounds, as candidates vied for the necessary absolute majorities in both bodies.

